FT  05 OCT 94 / World News in Brief: Reed Elsevier to pay Dollars 1.5bn for
US information group
Reed Elsevier, the Anglo-Dutch information and publishing group, said last
night it had reached agreement to pay Dollars 1.5bn (Pounds 950m) for the
electronic information arm of Mead Corporation, the US paper group.
Reed Elsevier is to acquire the assets of Mead Data Central, which operates
the on-line Lexis/Nexis legal and business publishing business. Reed
Elsevier plans to finance the acquisition from surplus cash and Dollars 1bn
in borrowings
